Another point: in Java, the array is 0-based, in Fortran it's 1-based. So in the loops, the Java code loops from 0 to n-1, Fortran loops from 1 to n.

But when translating, the code in the loops for the array a is correct. Wait, the Java code:

for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    a[i] = ...;
} In Fortran, the loop is do i = 1, n. But the array a in Java is size n. So in Fortran, a is allocated as a(n), and the loop runs from 1 to n. Each element is read correctly. Yes.
